replies.text:
To my knowledge, only one of the grills at the bottom of the phone holds a speaker. However, that speaker sounds quite nice. Gets pretty loud without distortion too. 
The dongle works just fine with regular 3.5mm headphones. Also used it with a car's aux cable and it sounded great! I prefer the lossless Type C headphones they included (there's actually a pretty significant difference, at least to my ears). Not to say the dongle+ regular headphones sound bad, just that the type c ones sound better. 
I am a recent convert to Action pro from Nova and both work perfectly;
